 CHAIRMAN of the Nigeria Union of Journalists, Benue State Chapter, Victoria Asher, is dead. Asher was said to have died at the Federal Medical Centre, Makurdi, after a caesarian section on Saturday. Her predecessor, David Ukuma, also died while in office as NUJ President. He served for less than six months before his demise. The Secretary of NUJ, Benue Council, Moses Akaahan, confirmed Asher’s death on Saturday, noting that she died at the Federal Medical Centre, around 8am on Saturday. He added that the Benue NUJ Council would issue a notice for an emergency congress, following the incident, in due course. Details later… 